CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 22, 1969, pg. 10, reads: "Admiring Gifts - Little Robin Bullard is pictured admiring some of the lovely gifts which she received on her 11th birthday. The party was given by Mrs. Margaret Bullard of Bedford Avenue who said it was for her 'favorite granddaughter.'  A number of Robin's friends were on hand to help her celebrate and all had loads of fun. - Harris photo."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Robin Bullard wearing party hat on her eleventh birthday, holding $25 United States savings bond, and seated on bed with gifts and cards, in bedroom of her grandmother, Margaret Bullard, 2801 Bedford Avenue
